lesson.title: Lesson 1 - Intro to the QMV Process

atoms.title: Before You Start
atoms.text:
### Introduction
Lesson 1 will introduce you to the iterative process of questioning, modeling, and validation to data analysis and model building.

Many of you may have already taken a course in machine learning or data science or are familiar with machine learning models. 

In this lesson and course, we will take a more general approach, and our  goal is to get you to practice thinking in depth about a problem and coming up with your own solutions.

### Software and Downloads
Please install the following list of software so you can follow along Don in lesson 1:

1. [Python](https://www.python.org/)
2. [Pandas](http://pandas.pydata.org/)
3. [Scikit-Learn](http://scikit-learn.org/stable/)
4. [Seaborn](http://stanford.edu/~mwaskom/software/seaborn/)

Lesson Code and Dataset:

1. [Lesson 1 Ipython Notebook](https://www.udacity.com/api/nodes/3616038658/supplemental_media/udacity-lesson1ipynb/download)
2. [Lesson 1 Dataset](https://www.udacity.com/api/nodes/3616038658/supplemental_media/candy-choicescsv/download)
